<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf0347840-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s8201"><num value="8201">§ 8201.</num><heading> Definitions</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In this chapter:</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I79" class="indent3 firstIndent-2" id="idf0347841-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s8201/1"><num value="1" class="bold">(1)</num><heading class="bold"> Eligible orchardist</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1">The term “eligible orchardist” means a person that produces annual crops from trees for commercial purposes.</p>
</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I79" class="indent3 firstIndent-2" id="idf0347842-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s8201/2"><num value="2" class="bold">(2)</num><heading class="bold"> Natural disaster</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1">The term “natural disaster” means plant disease, insect infestation, drought, fire, freeze, flood, earthquake, lightning, and other occurrence, as determined by the Secretary.</p>
</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I79" class="indent3 firstIndent-2" id="idf0347843-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s8201/3"><num value="3" class="bold">(3)</num><heading class="bold"> Secretary</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1">The term “Secretary” means the Secretary of Agriculture.</p>
</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I79" class="indent3 firstIndent-2" id="idf0347844-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s8201/4"><num value="4" class="bold">(4)</num><heading class="bold"> Tree</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1">The term “tree” includes a tree, bush, and vine.</p>
</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idf0347845-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/pl/107/171/tX/s10201">Pub. L. 107–171, title X, § 10201</ref>, <date date="2002-05-13">May 13, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/490">116 Stat. 490</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
